datafield.subfield: Dark Matter with multi-annihilation channels and AMS-02 positron excess and antiproton
Dark Matter with multi-annihilation channels and AMS-02 positron excess and antiproton

AMS-02 provided the unprecedented statistics in the measurement of the positron fraction from cosmic rays. That may offer a unique opportunity to distinguish the positron spectrum coming from various dark matter (DM) annihilation channels, if DM is the source of this positron excess. Therefore, we consider the scenario that the DM can annihilate into leptonic, quark, and massive gauge boson channels simultaneously with floating branching ratios to test this hypothesis. We also study the impacts from MAX, MED, MIN, and DC diffusion models as well as from isothermal, NFW, and Einasto DM density profiles on our results. We found two parameter regions that can satisfy both AMS-02 $\frac{e^+}{e^++e^-}$ and $\bar{p}/p$ datasets at 95\% CL. i) Under the NFW-MIN combination with $M_{\chi}\subset[10,30]$ TeV. ii) Under the Einasto-DC combination with $M_{\chi}\subset[500,1500]$ GeV.

00023 \small Left panel: the zoom-in of the island ($M_{\chi}\leq$ 1.6 TeV, $\left\langle \sigma v \right\rangle_{tot}\leq$ 2000 pb) at the lower-left corner of the upper-left panel of Fig.~\ref{EIN}. In the plane of ($M_{\chi},\, \left\langle \sigma v \right\rangle_{tot})$ the region bounded by the dashed contour satisfies both the AMS-02 $\frac{e^+}{e^++e^-}$ and the PAMELA $\bar{p}/p$ within 95\% CL. Right panel: the red dots are the PAMELA $\bar{p}/p$ data~\cite{pamela_antip}. The dashed curve is the $\bar{p}/p$ background model from Ref.~\cite{proton_bkgd,antiproton_bkgd}. The blue solid curve is the sum of background with the DM contribution, with $M_{\chi}$ = 673 GeV, $\left\langle \sigma v \right\rangle_{tot}$ = 429 pb with branching ratios $\textrm{BR}(\tau^+\tau^-, \mu^+\mu^-, e^+e^-, t\bar{t})$ = 82.81\%, 8.58\%, 8.59\%, 0.01\% respectively, and the other channels $\textrm{BR}(W^+W^-, ZZ, b\bar{b})\, <$ 0.01\%. The fit gives $\chi^2/dof$ = 31.97/36 and the $p$-value = 0.661 for AMS-02 $\frac{e^+}{e^++e^-}$ dataset; $\chi^2/dof$ = 6.72/3 and the $p$-value = 0.0815 for the PAMELA $\bar{p}/p$ dataset.
